    "summary": "This section answers retrieval queries regarding:\n- **Topics & Claims:** What are the 2022–2025 trends in overseas mobile game market revenue and download volumes? Why is download share shifting from Google Play to App Store, and what strategic implications does this iOS ecosystem migration have for game developers?\n- **Entities & Dates:** Which platforms (Google Play, App Store), regions (overseas, excluding mainland China), and timeframes (2022, 2023, 2024, 2025, with a 2026 data adjustment note) are covered?\n- **Definitions:** How are \"overseas mobile game market\" and \"revenue scale\" defined? (Scope limited to App Store and Google Play titles outside mainland China; revenue includes only direct user spending, explicitly excluding ad monetization and third-party top-ups).\n- **Procedures:** What user acquisition and store optimization actions should developers prioritize in response to platform shifts? (Increase focus on App Store product page optimization, localization, and editorial feature acquisition, elevating these to strategic parity with paid user acquisition).\n- **Tables & Figures:** What do the two bar charts illustrate? (Chart 1: 2022–2025 revenue in 亿元 for both platforms with overall market growth rates; Chart 2: 2022–2025 download volumes in 亿次, platform share percentages, and overall market growth rates).\n- **Metrics:** What specific quantitative values are tracked? (Annual revenue and download volumes per platform, platform share percentages, and year-over-year overall market growth rates ranging from -6.21% to 5.42%).\n- **Evidence Types:** What data sources and methodologies support the findings? (Diandian Data statistical models, corporate financial reports, expert interviews, and proprietary chart visualizations)."
